  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. A linear function can be written in the form <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of x  equals, m x plus b\"></span>, where <span class=\"italic\">m</span> is the slope and <span class=\"italic\">b</span> is the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-coordinate of the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-intercept of the line. The slope of the graph can be found using the formula <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals, the fraction with numerator y sub 2 minus y sub 1, and denominator x sub 2 minus x sub 1, end fraction\"></span>. Substituting the values of the given points into this formula yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals, the fraction with numerator negative 5 minus 3, and denominator 4 minus negative 2, end fraction \"></span> or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals, negative 8 over 6\"></span>, which simplifies to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals, negative four thirds\"></span>. Only choice C shows an equation with this slope.<br><br>Choices A, B, and D are incorrect and may result from computation errors or misinterpreting the given information.</p>\n",
